uientry.s:
local this = UIComponent(Address)
function ShowMenu(name) for i = 0, this:ChildCount() - 1 do local child = UIComponent(this:Find(i)) child:SetVisible(child:Id() == name) end end

uientry.unicode: Choose a battle map from the options below.||The map description tab to the right will give you details on the selected map to help you make your choice.
As you select a map from below, the map description tab to the right will provide details about it.

This is the maximum number of players available for this map.||Each player will control a different army.||Some maps have more than two players.||If there aren't enough players for the battle you can use AI players instead.

uientry.unicode: This setting provides you with different time periods to choose from.||Each period has units specific to that time.||Generally, the later periods will provide you with a larger choice of units.||Select a period according to your personal preferences.

uientry.unicode: Certain weather conditions will affect the way you fight a battle.||Heavy rain can dampen firearms - resulting in slower firing rates and even misfires.||A soggy battlefield will prevent cannonballs from bouncing, meaning they will not travel as far and do less damage.||Movement can be affected as well - for example, heavy snowfalls will slow down an army as it struggles through it.
